  "architecture": {
    "narrative": "This is a Node.js/Express REST API application following a classic three-layer architecture: API controllers, service layer, and data access layer.\n\nThe API layer (src/api/) defines Express route handlers that validate incoming requests and delegate to service classes. Each resource (users, auth) has its own route module, composed together in the API index.\n\nThe service layer (src/services/) contains all business logic. Services are stateless classes that coordinate between repositories and utility modules. The UserService handles account lifecycle, AuthService manages JWT authentication, and NotificationService dispatches emails.\n\nThe data layer uses Prisma ORM with the repository pattern. Each entity has a dedicated repository class that encapsulates database queries. A shared Prisma singleton manages the connection pool.\n\nUtility modules provide cross-cutting concerns: password hashing (bcrypt), JWT management, and email delivery (SendGrid). Configuration is centralized in a Zod-validated environment loader.",
